 to boycott ugliness in the name of beauty. Striving for something else than pure functionality in architecture, Krier calls for poetical approach, so characteristic for his work, stating: Poetry is in the breath of the building, the aroma that exudes from all its nooks". Rob Krier is one of the most influential architects and urban planners of the second half of the 20th century. His theoretical writings deal with the idea of town planning informed by traditional notions of harmony, civic space and community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh  aArchitecture, Contemporary Architects, Theory of Architecture, Urban Design.0 cEPUBz978311047056740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110438291zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110438291zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110438291.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA